summary: holy hell i love the continuation of ceo!harry kissing his assistant. can you please add part 3???? no pressure or anything i...
question: holy hell i love the continuation of ceo!harry kissing his assistant. can you please add part 3???? no pressure or anything i just love your writing so much ❣️
answer:
“am i still you’re plus-one?”

harry’s staying up late at his office in hopes sarah would call him back that y/n’s there, but after thinking about it that she probably wouldn’t, he took it upon himself to ring your office number in hopes too that you’d be there — and you actually did.

“harry?”

there’s certainly confusion in your tone on why he’s calling you on your landline at 10 in the evening, but then it sinks that your office landlines are the only numbers known in between the two of you, but then it sinks in him too on why you’re still there at that time of the night.

“hi! i was wondering if i was still your plus-one?”

he’s scratching at the back of his neck, tapping his rings against his table paying no mind at your confused answer the first time but he says it again less rushed and more coherent now.

“would you want to be?”

harry stammered at your question that’s turned back to him, sitting up straighter and the movement of his chair could be he heard at the other side of the line.

“o-of course! not unless you don’t want me to be! sarah said you had a lunch date and i assumed you’re dating that person and would rather go with them instead, so i was just-…”

“didn’t really have a lunch date,” you winced on the phone because of the lie your assistant brought on which you are now obligated to keep up with for the sake of consistency, but you can’t help to be a bit truthful either.

“you didn’t?”

“it’s complicated.”

harry hums to the phone and diverts his attention instead to his original question he intended to ask, nervous now that he’s gonna repeat it for the third time.

“am i your plus-one?”

“would it be okay with your assistant?”

y/n asked back again to him and he wants to groan now that he thinks of what happened awhile ago, grumbling something under his breath flusteredly as he did dismiss his previous intentions with her awhile ago when remorse settled in.

“not together. don’t — s’complicated too but we’re not a thing, or like never gonna be and stuff.”

both CEOs bask in the comfortable silence until y/n breaks it, taking pity on how harry’s gonna ask for the fourth time because that’s what e originally called floor and the focus shifts again after every time.

“harry?”

she’s call out to be reminded that he’s still there and he alertedly calls her name back which is now stupid because he thinks he should’ve just played it off with a cool “hmm?” or “yeah?” and it’s too late.

y/n keeps a little smile on her face, turning her chair to face the skyline in her office’s view all the while harry’s doing the same while waiting for her, both having the intentions to stay up late for this conversation even if they wouldn’t fully admit it to themselves.

“need you to wear white. we’re the only ones in that color and we need to be sort of paralled with what we wear?”

“should i bring matching corsages?”

he can’t help but to ask and y/n snorts at his teasing answer, but even if she’d actually say yes, he wouldn’t really mind.

“no. we just need matching designs and we’re gonna meet up for that tomorrow. i’ll fax you the details. good night, harry.”

harry smiles at his shot of redemption that’s halfway into being thrown before he can say he made a home-run, biting his lip unconsciously.

“good night, bub.”

question: Do you think Harry can be an ENFJ? I read a Tumblr post that made a good argument about it, but then again, I don't know much about the MBTI. To me he seems too reserved to Fe-dom, because after all, how much do we really know about his personal life?
answer:
So I’m almost positive that you sent this no less than eight million years ago, but I’m just getting around to it now because I’m a menace to society and that’s how I run things.

I’ve got a tag in which I talk about Harry’s possible MBTI results, and you can find that here. I wrote a longer post that details exactly why I think Harry is an INFP, and you can find that here.

Once again, like you said, it’s all speculation, because we don’t really know all that much about his personal life. However, based on my stance, that’s what I’ve come up with!

summary:
request: what if the fans that met harry backstage witnessed all the soft and fluffy moments between the missus and harry
You...
body:
request: what if the fans that met harry backstage witnessed all the soft and fluffy moments between the missus and harry

You were doing again your original thing whenever you’re waiting the show to finish, seat on the couch maybe do some work done and sometimes looking backstage to support your lovely boyfriend.

You also knew he was gonna meet some fans later so you just stayed in his dressing room so Harry and the girls won’t be disturbed or distracted, you want them to have the time of their lives. You planned to go out from the room for a minute to get yourself some water, you walked over the counter to go grab it, but it immediately stop your movements when Harry shouted your name.

“Y/N! Baby!” He ran over to you and pulled you for a hug, but pulling away sooner as you smelled sweat all over his body, he laughed and pressed a sweet kiss on the forehead before heading in into his dressing room. You laughed on how happy he was acting right now, sometimes you wish that you could even see a bigger smile on his face.

“You guys finished already?” You stood in front of Adam and Mitch as they took off their earplugs.

“Yeah, Harry ran pretty fast.” Mitch chuckled, you just nodded your head and finally turning around to find Sarah fixing her drumsticks. You gave her a tight hug and just started to talk about the show, you were a big fan because of her great skills.

A light gasp came out from your lips as you felt someone’s arms wrapping around your hips, and planted kisses just below your jawline. You tried wiggling out from his grasp, because you both know that was your ticklish part.

“Stop, oh my god.” Harry was quickly to turn you around so your head is now facing his shoulders, he is starting to smell good because of his cologne. He planted kisses on your shoulders, while you’re struggling to find a way out.

You guys were both swaying around the whole backstage because of your wiggling and laughters, but Harry’s band mates didn’t bother disturbing since they’re really used to this kind of view.

“You’re gonna have—Oh my god!—blue—“ You tried to say but your loud laughter made it hard to talk and you were sure it’s echoing around the room, but Harry still continued to do his tickiling-job.

“Hmm? Can’t hear ye’, babe.” He grinned at your skin completely trying not to laugh so much.

You both were interrupted when someone coughed which made you both freeze in your spot, when you felt his grip around you starting to loose, you quickly went out from his hold and finally looking in front of Harry. It was Jeff and some fans inside, holding their phones out, recording everything.

You brought your face into your hands, completely embarrassed. You didn’t expect this to happened at all. Harry laughed and put his hands on top of your shoulder, bringing you close to him.

“Hello! This is my lovely wife, Y/N.” He said it as if it was a true and normal thing for you. Your eyes widened at the word ‘Wife’ which made you slap his tummy, making Harry giggle and hug you again. You groaned as you just hid yourself on his chest, not wanting to be shown anymore.

‘Aww’s and ‘Oh my god’s were heard as Harry swayed you around trying to make you feel better but you didn’t move or anything, and it’s enough words for Harry to know you’re starting not to feel comfortable.

“Okay, let’s get you back inside, love.” He whispered and finally walking you to his dressing room.

Harry walked back again where his fans were, he did his usual thing, hugging them, thanking them, and getting the flowers they bought for him.

“So, she’s the wife?” The fan joked, making Harry laugh as he dropped the Vinyl that he signed and looked at her.

“Don’t rush love, but yeah, she will be soon.”

Harry walked back again where his fans were, he did his usual thing, hugging them, thanking them, and getting the flowers they bought for him.

“So, she’s the wife?” The fan joked, making Harry laugh as he dropped the Vinyl that he signed and looked at her.

“Don’t rush love, but yeah, she will be soon.”

You planned to go out from the room for a minute to get yourself some water, you walked over the counter to go grab it, but it immediately stop your movements when Harry shouted your name.

“Y/N! You laughed on how happy he was acting right now, sometimes you wish that you could even see a bigger smile on his face.

“You guys finished already?” You stood in front of Adam and Mitch as they took off their earplugs.

“Yeah, Harry ran pretty fast.” Mitch chuckled, you just nodded your head and finally turning around to find Sarah fixing her drumsticks. You gave her a tight hug and just started to talk about the show, you were a big fan because of her great skills.
